cs.AI, cs.LO, cs.DB, cs.CL, cs.CR 

This paper deals with knowledge representation and reasoning, which is a core topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). It specifically focuses on Description Logics (DLs), which are used for knowledge representation and reasoning in various applications such as databases (cs.DB) and natural language processing (cs.CL). The paper also discusses the decidability and decision procedures for the knowledge base satisfiability problem, which falls under the category of computational complexity theory (cs.CR). Finally, the paper deals with the extension of DLs to handle more expressive features, which is related to logic (cs.LO).
